74.0	Tom_Robbins	Tom Robbins	Thomas Eugene "Tom" Robbins (born July 22, 1936) is an American author. His best-selling novels are seriocomic , often wildly poetic stories with a strong social and philosophical undercurrent, an irreverent bent, and scenes extrapolated from carefully researched bizarre facts . He is probably best known for his novel Even Cowgirls Get the Blues which was made into a movie in 1993 by Gus Van Sant and starring Uma Thurman, Lorraine Bracco and Keanu Reeves.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3b/Tom_Robbins.jpg/175px-Tom_Robbins.jpg
